#dropping irrelevant columns from each crypto df and renaming the column

for x,y in zip(list,list_cp):
    globals()[y] = globals()[x].drop(columns=['SNo','Name','Symbol','Open','Volume'])
    globals()[y].rename(columns = {'Close': x.upper()},inplace=True)

Standardising the dates in each df and merging the df¶

In [18]:
#creating copies to preserve the original data

closing_price_master = closing_price_crypto.copy(deep=True)
In [19]:
#iterating through and cleaning the dates in the crypto df

for y,z in zip(closing_price_master['Date'],range(0,len(closing_price_master['Date']))):
    p = dt.datetime.strptime(y,'%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')
    closing_price_master.iloc[z,0] = p.date()
    z=z+1
In [20]:

In [29]:
#populating the daily price change % columns

for x in day_change_cp_master['BTC']:
    day_change_cp_master['BTC_dc'] = (day_change_cp_master['BTC'] - (day_change_cp_master['BTC'].shift(1)))/day_change_cp_master['BTC']

for x in day_change_cp_master['ETH']:
    day_change_cp_master['ETH_dc'] = (day_change_cp_master['ETH'] - (day_change_cp_master['ETH'].shift(1)))/day_change_cp_master['ETH']

for x in day_change_cp_master['XRP']:
    day_change_cp_master['XRP_dc'] = (day_change_cp_master['XRP'] - (day_change_cp_master['XRP'].shift(1)))/day_change_cp_master['XRP']

Dropping outliers of the prices of each variable¶

In [50]:
#creating a new df without the outliers

closing_price_master_no_outliers = closing_price_master.copy(deep=True)



#dropping outliers in the new df using inter-quartile range as a parameter

for x,y in zip(range(1,9),range(0,7)):
    Q1 = np.percentile(closing_price_master_no_outliers.iloc[:,x], 25,
                       interpolation = 'midpoint')

    Q3 = np.percentile(closing_price_master_no_outliers.iloc[:,x], 75,
                       interpolation = 'midpoint')
    IQR = Q3 - Q1

    print("Old Shape: ", closing_price_master_no_outliers.shape)

    # Upper bound
    upper = np.where(closing_price_master_no_outliers.iloc[:,x] >= (Q3+5*IQR))
    # Lower bound
    lower = np.where(closing_price_master_no_outliers.iloc[:,x] <= (Q1-5*IQR))

    closing_price_master_no_outliers.drop(upper[0], inplace = True)
    closing_price_master_no_outliers.drop(lower[0], inplace = True)
    closing_price_master_no_outliers.reset_index(inplace=True)
    closing_price_master_no_outliers.drop(columns='index',inplace=True)

    print("New Shape: ", closing_price_master_no_outliers.shape)

Dropping outliers of the daily price change % variables¶

In [59]:
#creating a new df without the outliers

day_change_cp_master_no_outliers = day_change_cp_master.copy(deep=True)



#dropping outliers in the new df using inter-quartile range as a parameter

for x,y in zip(range(1,9),range(0,7)):
    Q1 = np.percentile(day_change_cp_master_no_outliers.iloc[:,x], 25,
                       interpolation = 'midpoint')

    Q3 = np.percentile(day_change_cp_master_no_outliers.iloc[:,x], 75,
                   interpolation = 'midpoint')
    IQR = Q3 - Q1

    print("Old Shape: ", day_change_cp_master_no_outliers.shape)

# Upper bound
    upper = np.where(day_change_cp_master_no_outliers.iloc[:,x] >= (Q3+5*IQR))
# Lower bound
    lower = np.where(day_change_cp_master_no_outliers.iloc[:,x] <= (Q1-5*IQR))

    day_change_cp_master_no_outliers.drop(upper[0], inplace = True)
    day_change_cp_master_no_outliers.drop(lower[0], inplace = True)
    day_change_cp_master_no_outliers.reset_index(inplace=True)
    day_change_cp_master_no_outliers.drop(columns='index',inplace=True)

    print("New Shape: ", day_change_cp_master_no_outliers.shape)
